                <!-- Long-term Health Effects -->
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e3f2fd, #bbdefb); border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0;">
                    <h3>üß¨ Long-term Health Effects</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <h4>Chronic Conditions from Food Poisoning:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Reactive Arthritis:</strong> Joint pain lasting months or years</li>
                            <li><strong>Chronic Kidney Disease:</strong> From E. coli O157:H7 infections</li>
                            <li><strong>Neurological Disorders:</strong> Nerve damage, paralysis from botulism</li>
                            <li><strong>Digestive Problems:</strong> Irritable bowel syndrome, food intolerances</li>
                            <li><strong>Immune System Damage:</strong> Reduced white blood cell function</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Cellular Damage -->
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff3e0, #ffe0b2); border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0;">
                    <h3>üß¨ Cellular Level Damage</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <h4>How Toxins Damage Your Body:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>DNA Damage:</strong> Aflatoxins cause genetic mutations leading to cancer</li>
                            <li><strong>Mitochondrial Destruction:</strong> Interferes with cellular energy production</li>
                            <li><strong>Immune Suppression:</strong> Reduces white blood cell function by up to 70%</li>
                            <li><strong>Neurological Impact:</strong> Toxins cross blood-brain barrier causing cognitive decline</li>
                            <li><strong>Organ Damage:</strong> Liver, kidney, and heart damage from chronic exposure</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Special Populations -->
                <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e8f5e9, #c8e6c9); border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px; margin: 15px 0;">
                    <h3>üë∂ Special Populations at Risk</h3>
                    <div style="background: white; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; margin: 10px 0;">
                        <h4>High-Risk Groups:</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Infants under 1 year:</strong> NO honey - risk of infant botulism (can be fatal)</li>
                            <li><strong>Pregnant Women:</strong> Listeria can cause miscarriage and stillbirth</li>
                            <li><strong>Elderly over 65:</strong> Weakened immune systems, higher mortality rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Cancer Patients:</strong> Chemotherapy weakens immune response</li>
                            <li><strong>Diabetics:</strong> Higher risk of complications from foodborne illness</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

